{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"18e4dc34-c268-4c34-88a3-9f0cc11e858a","content":"Run **`dotnet workload update`**.\n\n- **`dotnet workload update`** – downloads and installs the latest versions of all installed workloads, aligning them with your current SDK. This is what you need after an SDK update.\n\n- **`dotnet workload repair`** – reinstalls the *same* versions already recorded; it fixes corrupted or missing files but doesn't upgrade anything.\n\nSince your issue is a version mismatch (old workload vs. new SDK), `update` is the correct choice:\n\n```bash\ndotnet workload update\n```\n\nIf it still fails afterward, also verify your MAUI workload is installed:\n\n```bash\ndotnet workload list\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"cfbd26bc-7532-431e-999c-fd0880b32919","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about the difference between `dotnet workload update` and `dotnet workload repair` to fix a .NET MAUI build issue after an SDK update. This is a general knowledge question that I can answer directly without needing to search files or run commands.","outputTokens":234,"requestId":"9432:1DC2AE:14958A2:16FAC09:6A06703D"},"id":"dd88e2a4-446b-47dd-a0b5-d422ccefa318","timestamp":"2026-05-15T01:00:52.361Z","parentId":"c7985f17-2f02-4084-af81-ed13c04049c8"}
